@{FG Shine}Welcome to @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 3rd issue of @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.

Summer. Special time to rest. So, it's usual that nothing happens in Summer. But
this is not the case in the @{B}Amiga@{UB} world. And specially this year.

Since  @{B}Commodore@{UB}'s  bankruptcy,  we  have  seen  the  closures  of so many @{B}Amiga@{UB}
magazines:  @{B}Amiga  World@{UB},  @{B}Amiga User International@{UB}, @{B}Amiga Shopper@{UB}, @{B}Amiga Power@{UB},
only  to name a few of them. The usual reason of these closures were the lack of
advertizers and/or readers.

This  was  not  the  case  of  @{B}CU-Amiga@{UB}.  It is the best selling @{B}Amiga@{UB} magazine.
However, the October's issue will be the last of @{B}CU@{UB}.

I  remember  the first magazine I bought. It was the May's issue of @{B}CU-Amiga@{UB}, in
1990.  It  costed me 720 ptas (around 2.85£ at that time). It was mostly a games
magazine (it covered games as @{B}Their Finest Hour@{UB}, @{B}Persian Gulf Inferno@{UB} and @{B}Tennis
Cup@{UB}).  Since then, @{B}CU-Amiga@{UB} has evolved a lot, and its quality has been improved
a lot. I think it is (or was) the perfect magazine.

I  feel that this last issue will be something not to be missed. Here, in Spain,
it  is  not easy to find it, so I will try to contact the @{B}CU@{UB} staff, just in case
it is possible to buy it as a back issue. I heard that @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} will give them
an  exclusive  news  and  the CU-CD will feature something that needs the @{B}Sony@{UB}'s
permission.

Anyway,  this  is  not the end of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. We have @{B}Amiga Format@{UB}, the other big
magazine.  It  is  a  very  good  magazine, so I recommend all the @{B}CU@{UB} readers to
subscribe  @{B}Amiga Format@{UB}. In my case, I have just suscribed to the 3rd attempt to
do  a  spanish  @{B}Amiga@{UB} magazine. Its name: @{B}mundo Amiga@{UB}. If you speak Spanish, for
more information about this new magazine, visite

        @{B}http://soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/noticias/980909_mundoami.html@{UB}

and then subscribe.

Talking  about  the  features of this issue, I apologize because it has not been
possible  to bring you the promised interview. And although this issue was going
to  have Football as the main topic, the soon-to-be-released @{B}Samba World Cup@{UB} and
@{B}Eat the Whistle@{UB} have made me to wait, so I expect to bring you a review of these
games in future issues.

Remember to visit the @{B}SAUG@{UB} website, which is located in:

        @{B}http://www.saug.com/sau/@{UB}

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

        @{B}http://soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/@{UB}

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

        @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
@{I}Angel Alvarez Díaz @{UI} - @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}
Member of @{B}C.U.A.E@{UB} Nº 293 - @{I}FOREIGN DIRECTOR @{UI}
Responsible of the News Departament of @{B}S.A.U.@{UB} and @{B}Amiga Channel@{UB}.
Editor of the e-magazine called @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.
