@node not01 "STFAX PROFESSIONAL V3.3 SUPPORTS INDEPENDENT OPERATION MODE"

@{B}STFAX PROFESSIONAL V3.3@{UB} SUPPORTS @{I}INDEPENDENT OPERATION MODE@{UI}
-----------------------------------------------------------

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

@{I}@{B}STFax Professional V3.3@{UB} supports Independent Operation Mode@{UI}

The  recently  released  @{B}STFax  Professional  v3.3@{UB}  now supports the @{I}Independent
Operation  Mode@{UI}  found  within  the  @{B}PACE  'Solo'@{UB}  (www.pacecom.co.uk) and @{B}3-Com
Message Plus@{UB} modems.

@{I}Independent  Operation  Mode@{UI} allows you to use the modem as a digital answer and
fax  machine  without  the need for your @{B}Amiga@{UB} to be switched on! The modem will
answer  with  a  greeting, the caller can leave a message as per a normal answer
machine and, if they are sending a fax, the modem will automatically switch into
fax mode and receive the fax transmission.

These voice and fax messages are then stored on the modem and, the next time you
run  your @{B}Amiga@{UB} and @{B}STFax Professional@{UB} (@{B}v3.3+@{UB}), these messages are automatically
downloaded  to  your  machine.  You  are then able to play/view/print/delete the
messages.

@{B}STFax  Professional@{UB}  supports  the  more  advanced  @{I}Independent  Operation  Mode@{UI}
features  only found within the @{B}PACE 'Solo'@{UB} modem. For instance you can remotely
retrieve  you  messages,  you can use the 'follow me' option to call you on your
mobile and play important messages and so on.

Please  note: that you need the @{B}PACE 'Solo'@{UB} or @{B}3-Com Message Plus@{UB} modem in order
to  use the independent support within @{B}STFax Professional v3.3+@{UB}. We currently do
not  support the @{B}Olitec 56K@{UB} or the new @{B}3-Com Professional Message Plus@{UB} modem. We
hope to add support for these modems in the future, within a new update.

@{I}@{B}NetConnect v2@{UB} Special Pre-Order Price Available@{UI}

The long awaited @{B}NetConnect v2@{UB} is due for release on the 21st of April 1998. You
can pre-order the new CD before release and save £10.

@{B}NetConnect  v2@{UB}  is  the  easiest  and  most  comprehensive  Internet compilation
designed  to enable any @{B}Amiga@{UB} user, from novice to expert level, to get onto and
use the Internet.

The  CD  is  based  around  eleven commercial programs, debuting @{B}AmiTCP-Genesis@{UB},
@{B}X-Arc@{UB},  @{B}Microdot-II  v1@{UB}  and  @{B}Vapor@{UB}'s new @{B}Contact Manager@{UB}. You are given all you
will  need to get the most from the Internet. By using the new @{B}Genesis Wizard@{UB}, a
user  should  be  able connect to the Internet in a matter of minutes. Ideal for
both  an  Internet and/or local area network connection (due to @{B}Genesis@{UB}' ability
to  support  multiple interface connections) and for an advanced or novice @{B}Amiga@{UB}
Internet user.

