WILL @{B}WIPEOUT 2097@{UB} AND @{B}TOMB RAIDER@{UB} PORTED TO THE @{B}AMIGA@{UB}?
------------------------------------------------------

@{B}Statement from Digital Images.@{UB}

@{B}Digital Images@{UB} is a new games and software development company for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. We
aim  to  make  things  different  and  better  for  the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. We have our first
original  strategy  business  sim on the way, @{B}Space Station 3000@{UB}. After that, we
intend  to  convert  some  of the @{B}PC@{UB}'s finest games to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. The first 2 of
which  are @{B}Wipeout 2097@{UB} which is a brilliant 3D racing game for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} set in
the  future.  The  other  one  is  @{B}Tomb  Raider  3@{UB}. @{B}Tomb Raider 3@{UB} isn't actually
released  yet,  but  we think that @{B}Amiga@{UB} owners should enjoy this fabalous game.
The main problem is, the companies that own the rights to these games need to be
shown  that  there  is  still a market for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}, and within 18 months, that
market will start returning to a good strength.

The  reason @{B}Myst@{UB} and @{B}Quake@{UB} were ported to the @{B}Amiga@{UB} was because of hassling from
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  owners.  @{B}ID  Software@{UB}  (The  copyright  owners  of  @{B}Quake@{UB})  and @{B}Cyan@{UB} (The
copyright  owners  of  @{B}Myst@{UB})  thought  that the @{B}Amiga@{UB} died out at the end of the
@{B}Commodore@{UB}  era. That is, until illegal demo's of both of these games appeared on
the  internet.  These  demo's soon got deleted from the internet after came from
both  of  the companies. But, the @{B}Amiga@{UB} owners who had seen them wanted the real
thing.  They  hassled  @{B}Cyan@{UB}  for  @{B}Myst@{UB} and @{B}ID@{UB} for @{B}Quake@{UB}. This is where @{B}ClickBOOM@{UB}
stepped in and bought the licencing.

What  I'm  trying  to  say  is,  that  you,  as @{B}Amiga@{UB} users need to hassle these
companies for these games. Only then, can we hope to succeed.

We  would like you to hassle @{B}Psygnosis@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} release of @{B}Wipeout 2097@{UB} and
we want you to hassle @{B}EIDOS@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} release of @{B}Tomb Raider 3@{UB}.

