children  to use it un aided. For example, in the drawing package, you only need
click the mouse once and it will draw continuosly until you press it again. This
is  essential  for  small  hands  so  they don't have to keep the button pressed
whilst  drawing. A full tutorial is provided at the start of each game courstesy
of  your friend - @{I}Adiboo@{UI}. He talks you through each game in detail and describes
what every icon is for. There is also a friendly worm to help you out if you get
stuck.

@{B}Adiboo@{UB} has been developed with full teachers support so you can feel safe in the
knowledge that your child is being taught according to the national curriculum.

@{B}Alive  Kids - Adiboo@{UB} comes packaged in a big gift box containing both CD's, full
colour manual and a free activity book and colouring crayons.

This  is  a complete conversion of the @{B}Macintosh@{UB} version onto the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. Minimum
specification required is @{B}Amiga '040@{UB} or @{B}PPC@{UB}, 8mb, Hard-drive and CDrom.

@{B}Adiboo@{UB} runs in 256 colour in a 640 x 480 screen. We recommend that you use a gfx
card but it`s not essential.

@{B}Alive@{UB}  kids  software  will revolutionise childrens software on the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. Never
again  will  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  be  left  behind  by  other  platforms  - we've had the
capabilities for years and now we have the software.

@{B}Adiboo@{UB} is fully upgradable by way of future upgrades and add-ons.

No price has been confirmed as yet.

More  details  about  @{B}Adiboo@{UB}  and  other  releases  can  be found in our 16 page
