@node not46 "TITAN COMPUTER GIVE US SOME ANSWERS"

@{B}TITAN COMPUTER@{UB} GIVE US SOME ANSWERS
--------------------------------------------

The biggest news for most of the @{B}Amiga@{UB} community was the @{B}Computer '98@{UB} release of
@{B}Evils  Doom SE@{UB}, an RPG originally released as shareware. Available in English or
German, the game boasts an improved 3D engine, and nice graphics and animations.
A  demo  of  @{B}Evils  Doom  SE@{UB}  (their  last  @{B}68k@{UB}  project for the moment) will be
available next month, keep an eye on @{B}Titan@{UB}'s web site (see below).

In  the  only  non-gaming news to emerge, @{B}BurnIt@{UB}, their CD writer software, will
also be recieving an update soon.

Also  due for release at @{B}Computer '98@{UB} will be the @{B}Tomb Raider@{UB} clone @{B}Claws of the
Devil@{UB}.  The game will feature horror elements and is likely to be 100% PPC code.
Sales  figures  for  this  game  will  influence  the  development  of two other
projects,  @{B}Total  Combustion  PPC@{UB}  (a  @{B}Carmageddon@{UB}  clone)  and @{B}The Last Days of
Paradise  PPC@{UB} (a space action game). They're looking for sales figures of around
2000 for @{B}Claws of the Devil@{UB} before they come to any decision on these games.

And  @{B}Titan@{UB}  also  put  an  end to speculation by announcing that there will be a
@{B}Shadow  Of  The Third Moon 2 PPC@{UB}. @{B}Black Blade@{UB}, who developed the original @{B}SOTTM@{UB},
were  tremendously  unlucky  with  piracy  figures, and it was claimed that they
logged  three  downloads from a pirate "warez" site for every genuine copy sold.
They'll clearly be hoping for better this time round.

There's  also  a  big surprise planned for @{B}Computer '98@{UB}. They wouldn't, however,
drop any hints.

