@node not55 "PRELUDE1200: A SOUND CARD FOR THE A1200"

@{B}PRELUDE1200@{UB}: A SOUND CARD FOR THE @{B}A1200@{UB}
---------------------------------------

@{I}The internal @{B}A1200@{UB} version@{UI}

This  new  soundcard will plug into the @{B}A1200@{UB}'s realtime clock port along with a
connection  terminal  in  the  rear expansion booth. It has an active microphone
input  with  pre  amplifier  and power supply for condenser microphones. All the
other  features  are  almost identical to the 'big' @{B}Prelude@{UB}, e.g. true 44100 and
48000 Hz fullduplex, a multi channel mixer, record level adjustment, etc.

@{I}About  @{B}Prelude@{UB}'s  soundchip@{UI}  The  @{B}CS4231A@{UB}  from  @{B}Crystal@{UB}  is a combined encoder,
decoder  and  mixer  (CODEC)  especially  designed  for  high  quality  computer
soundcards  and  can be found on the @{B}Terratec Maestro@{UB} boards for example. It has
all  the  filters  and  a  high  accuracy  voltage  reference  already built in.
Additional  filters  on  the @{B}Prelude1200@{UB} board keep the noise down even further.
The soundchip is controlled by a new version of my fast @{B}ISA@{UB} bridge. Two separate
FIFOs for record and playback allow reliable full duplex operation at low system
load.

@{I}Full  @{B}AHI@{UB} support@{UI} Because @{B}Prelude 1200@{UB} is 99% hardware compatible with the @{B}Zorro@{UB}
version,  only  little  changes  have to be made to the drivers to archieve full
software  compatibility.  The  new  drivers  will  be  just  a few bytes larger,
autodetecting  which @{B}Prelude@{UB} model you have installed. In other words, no matter
which @{B}Prelude@{UB} you have, you can use the same drivers and the same software!

@{I}Current state of the project:@{UI}
 * First prototype is up and running!
 * A beta version of the @{B}AHI@{UB} driver is available, too.

