@node rc5 "THE AMIGA RC5 TEAM EFFORT NEWS"

AMIGA RC5 TEAM EFFORT NEWS
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
The following is from the @{B}Amiga RC5 Team@{UB} effort homepage at:
                @{B}http://www.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/rc5/@{UB}

03-Jul-98

Due  to  a  newly found security hole in the @{B}MicroSoft-IIS/4.0@{UB} server (so what's
new  :)  stats have been moved, hence the links were broken for a short time, if
you  have  scripts pointing towards them please change those. A note of reminder
that  @{B}DES II-2@{UB} starts ten days from now (13th July), so upgrade to a @{B}DES@{UB} capable
client  if  you  haven't  done  so  yet and set @{I}preferredcontest=2@{UI} (the upcoming
@{B}2.7100@{UB}  client  will have a slightly different @{I}.ini@{UI} file entry for this, more on
this when it becomes available). Also, the turnaround time for @{B}DES II-2@{UB} needs to
be  minimal,  since  redistribution of the keyspace is expected after around six
days  already,  so set your clients to fetch the smallest blocksize (228) and do
not  buffer more than you can do in one single day, preferably flush immediately
blocks are done (after the sixth day ideally flush after every block :). We look
like  catching  the @{B}Win32@{UB} team within a week too now if current differences keep
up, time to break out the champagne :)

12-Jul-98

Champagne  time!  We beat the @{B}Win32@{UB} team and are now ranked 6th overall, just in
time  for  the Monday start of @{B}DES II-2@{UB} :) Everyone tell the client to switch to
@{B}DES@{UB} on Monday (get a @{B}DES@{UB} capable client if you haven't got one yet), the interim
@{B}DES  II-2@{UB} challenge will only last 10 days or so, if not less. Another chance to
be  ranked  up  high,  perhaps  find  the  key. Don't worry about the @{B}Win32@{UB} team
catching  us in the meantime, we have plenty of time to make up for the ten days
of  @{B}DES  II-2@{UB}.  The  new @{B}2.7100@{UB} client should be very near approval now as well,
stay  tuned.  Also,  after some discussion on the mailinglist we have chosen the
@{B}Jay Miner Society@{UB} (@{B}http://www.jms.org/@{UB}) as our designated non-profit, as soon as
they  appear  in the non-profit list, please select them as benefactors (this is
separate  to  team attribution). Part of the prize money will go to them in case
they  get  enough votes (decided on the number of blocks attributed). While this
is not likely, it still means an @{B}Amiga@{UB} oriented non- profit will be in the list.

13-Jul-98

New  clients  out!  Just  in  time  for  the  @{B}DES  II-2@{UB} challenge start, clients
@{B}v2.7100.413@{UB}  are  out,  please  switch  ASAP, should cure the runoffline problem
amongst  others.  The  ini  file  format  has  changed  slightly, amongst others
'preferredcontest'  has  been replaced by 'processdes', set this to processdes=1
to automatically switch to @{B}DES II-2@{UB} when it starts Monday (this will happen when
you  first  contact  the proxies after the start of the challenge, so flush your
blocks Monday evening (18:00 CET at least)).

13-Jul-98

According  to  @{I}Stefan@{UI}  the  slight  @{B}RC5@{UB}  core slowdown is due to the rest of the
client,  major  cleanup  etc. For @{B}DES II-2@{UB} the latest client is fastest, so keep
using it! :) We should have first @{B}DES@{UB} statistics results early tomorrow morning,
the @{B}Bovine@{UB} effort in it's entirety is doing over 21 GKeys/s already only after a
couple  of  hours  of  the effort, whereas this took almost a week for @{B}DES II-1@{UB},
0.25%  of  the  keyspace  now returned, with 5.75% distributed (part of which is
probably  already  done,  but buffered). This is going to be quick, se get on it
NOW :)

14-Jul-98

The first stats are in, we are ranked 17th overall after the first day, which is
only  a couple of hours in reality, tomorrow we should have a clearer picture of
the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  team  performance. Only 100 people managed to flush blocks for this,
hopefully  this  will  improve soon as well. Remember to set E-mail address, the
new @{B}v2.7100@{UB} client does not have @{I}rc5@amiga.cistron.nl@{UI} as default!

14-Jul-98 (update)

Second  day  stats  are  in,  over 6% of keyspace done (current total rate: 46.7
Gkeys/s)  and  we  are up into the top 10 :) Looks like we are doing nicely, but
one  third of @{B}DES@{UB} blocks are coming from the older 7.021 client, which is slower
on    @{B}DES@{UB}    than    the    new    @{B}2.7100@{UB}    clients!    Switch   now!   Updated
@{B}http://homepage.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/rc5/corporate.html@{UB} Corporate Supporters page
to point to @{B}DES II-2@{UB} statistics.

15-Jul-98

Third  day  @{B}DES  II-2@{UB} stats are in, are you drunk yet? You should be, because we
passed  the @{B}Win32@{UB} team again :) Currently ranked 9th overall with a whopping 626
Mkeys/s  for  yesterday, 13.7% of the keyspace is done. Looking better every day
:)  @{I}Roberto  Patriarca@{UI}  (@{I}r.patriarca@flashnet.it@{UI}) has written a nice GUI for the
@{B}2.7100@{UB} client (not for earlier versions!) using @{B}MUI@{UB}, with oodles of options like
iconify, progress bars etc. Get it at @{B}http://pratesi.it/~patriot/myzar.lha@{UB}

16-Jul-98

Day  4: 22.2% of total keyspace done, it's an excitingly close battle. While our
rate  increased  slightly,  we  lost 400 blocks to the @{B}Win32@{UB} team yesterday, but
remained  9th  overall  and  gained  4000 blocks on the closely 8th placed @{B}Linux@{UB}
team. Whip those machines, only a couple of days left! :)

18-Jul-98

@{B}DES II-2@{UB} is over! That's right, @{B}DES II-2@{UB} has already been concluded in much less
than  the  projected ten days. Shame on you if you didn't do @{B}DES@{UB} because of @{B}RC5@{UB},
and  congrats  to everyone who participated for ranking us in a very visible 9th
overall spot.

The  actual finder of the key is not @{B}Distributed Net@{UB} however, but the @{B}Electronic
Frontier  Foundation@{UB},  or  @{B}EFF@{UB}  for  short,  a  non-profit organization which is
concerned with privacy and free speech issues on the Internet, amongst others.

They  built a special '@{B}DES@{UB} cracker' for about $250,000 which cracked @{B}DES II-2@{UB} in
56  hours,  or  almost  2.5 days. In the same period of time the @{B}Distributed Net@{UB}
effort  we  participate  in  did  somewhere in the region of 10-15% of that same
keyspace  and currently equals the @{B}'Deep Crack'@{UB} machine's power, while still 40%
of  the  machines  in  the  effort were doing @{B}RC5-64@{UB}. @{B}Distributed Net@{UB}'s power is
expected  to  grow  to  2.6  times  to that of @{B}'Deep Crack'@{UB} by the time @{B}DES II-3@{UB}
starts,  the  next  installment  of  @{B}RSA Labs'@{UB} series of challenges. (The @{B}Bovine@{UB}
effort lasted 4 days total because they waited for confirmation of @{B}RSA Labs@{UB} that
the @{B}EFF@{UB} found key was indeed the correct one.)

What  does  this  mean?  A  well  done  to  @{B}EFF@{UB}  for  showing a relatively small
non-profit  can  embarrass the US government in only 2,5 days (who contended for
years  that it would take multi million Dollar investments and months to do it),
the  same  to @{B}Distributed Net@{UB} for doing almost the same with just enthusiasm and
spare  cycles,  and  to  us,  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  team for ranking this high in spite of
everyone around us dressing black and holding their noses :)

Also,  some  well  deserved  exposure  for  the team and @{B}Amiga@{UB} in general, and a
little  regret  for  not  having  found the key ourselves (or getting more time,
since  we  looked to overtake @{B}Linux@{UB} team as well, in addition of the @{B}Win32@{UB} team,
perhaps even reaching the magical one Gigakey/s limit :)

What  next?  We  continue with @{B}RC5-64@{UB} of course, where we are ranked 6th overall
out of more than 3000 teams. You don't have to do anything special for this, the
client  @{B}v2.7100@{UB}  switches back to @{B}RC5-64@{UB} automatically when it connects again to
one  of the @{B}Bovine@{UB} proxies. Please delete any @{B}DES@{UB} blocks you still have buffered
as those are landfill now, and switch clients back to @{B}RC5-64@{UB} in case they didn't
by themselves.

19-Jul-98

@{B}RC5-64@{UB}  statistics  are  back.  We  are  still  ranked  6th overall and although
@{B}Slashdot.org@{UB}  is  making  uncannily  good  speed (they'll catch us in 10 days at
current  differences), we are doing better every day and looking like a possible
candidate  to  overtake  the  @{B}LinuxNET@{UB}  team sometime in the (hopefully) not too
distant future :)

24-Jul-98

The  currently  fastest  team,  @{B}Slashdot.org@{UB} passed us today, looks like the @{B}EFF@{UB}
crack  publicity  helped to more than double their rate. Congratulations to them
of  course, we need to shine by getting ourselves faster, not hoping others will
remain/get slower. We enjoyed 6th overall ranking for 12 days, and possibly will
again  as our rate is steadily increasing, more @{B}PowerPC@{UB} equipped @{B}Amigas@{UB} and more
machines  in  general  join  the  effort.  So,  the  moral of the story is: keep
cracking and get more people to join the team! If you are not on the mailinglist
yet,  join  the  discussion  now,  and participate in current topics such as the
cunning plans for using the @{B}Permedia 2@{UB} for bitslicing, etc. :)

03-Aug-98

@{I}Roberto  Patriarca@{UI} (@{I}r.patriarca@flashnet.it@{UI}) has updated the @{B}Myzar GUI@{UB} (now also
for  @{B}2.7100.405@{UB}  as well as newer, faster refresh, supports @{B}PPC@{UB} and @{B}AmiTCP@{UB}/@{B}Miami@{UB}
and  many  more).  Get  it  at @{B}http://pratesi.it/~patriot/myzar/myzar.lha@{UB}. Small
update  on  the rankings: we have consistently been doing over 300 Mkeys/s (with
now  more  than  20%  @{B}PPC@{B}  equipped  @{B}Amiga@{UB}s),  which means in time we will catch
@{B}LinuxNet@{UB}  and  move  back  up  to 6th. At current rates that's still more than 3
months  though,  which means we are still growing but we could do that faster :)
So  again a call to arms, tell everyone and get them in on the effort! Also, the
next update of the client is being worked on as we speak, more about that later.

20-Aug-98

Today The @{B}Amiga RC5 Team@{UB} effort is celebrating its first anniversary!

We  started  off  after  a 'cool, let's do this' session on IRC with a couple of
machines  and look where that got us <G>. A Press Release will go out shortly on
this,  spread the word! This is also an excellent time to alert mainstream media
and  hopefully  get  a  mention  of  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  and  how things _can_ boom on a
supposedly dead platform if the enthusiasm is there..

Note on the mail flushing mechanism (most people use the client to flush, ignore
this  bit  unless  you  can only use E-mail to fetch/flush): the engine has been
revised/rewritten,  not  all  functionality  has  been  reimplemented yet but it
should  be  a  lot faster now. It can currently only handle MIME attached base64
encoded     buffer     files     (apart     from     this    restriction,    see
@{B}http://www.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/misc/blocksbymail.txt@{UB}    explanation   for   this
mechanism)

21-Aug-98

Three  hoorays  for  @{B}Justin  Pope@{UB}  (@{B}http://www.galstar.com/~jupo/@{UB}) and the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
community  spirit!  He kindly donated a replacement drive (3.5 GB IDE) after the
main  'effort  HD' started dying last week. A nice effort birthday gift :) Today
we  also  broke the 400 Mkey/s barrier and ranked 5th daily with that, way to go
team!

23-Aug-98

The  second percent of the keyspace has been searched. Whereas the first percent
took  seven  months,  the second one took only three, illustrating the growth of
the overall effort (which is still way ahead of @{I}Moore@{UI}'s Law). Continuing at this
rate  we  will  have  done  3% in about 2 more months and getting similar growth
rates  further  on. Although it's still too early to speculate on whether growth
rates  keep  up,  or  will  possibly  increase,  methods  based on linear growth
calculation  predict  that we will have found the right key during the year 2000
or  2001.  Also  for  yesterday  we  ranked third overall with an impressive 453
Mkeys/s,  doing  nearly  twice  as much blocks as @{B}LinuxNet@{UB}, whom we should catch
before the 3% mark :)

23-Aug-98 (update)

Finally   added   PR   on   the   first   anniversary   in   the  press  section
(@{B}http://www.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/press.html@{UB}), time to bombard the media! :)

28-Aug-98

@{B}Myzar@{UB},  the GUI frontend has been updated, check out the "Miscellaneous" section
(@{B}http://www.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/misc.html@{UB}) for the changes and where to download
