@node art01 "AMIWEST '98 SHOW REPORT FROM ASHA DEVELDER"

@{B}AMIWEST '98@{UB} SHOW REPORT FROM @{I}ASHA DEVELDER@{UI}
------------------------------------------

13-Jul-98 02:00:01

Subject: @{B}AmiWest '98@{UB}
From: @{I}Asha DeVelder@{UI}/SYSOP 76703,4322
To: @{I}All@{UI}

I've been back from @{B}AmiWest '98@{UB} for a few hours now. It was hot. :)

The  show was held in the Ramada Inn in Sacremento. The Inn is a small hotel but
cozy.  @{B}AmiWest@{UB}  took  up (at least) three rooms for the three day show. The main
room had about two dozen (guesstimate) boths and there were two seminar rooms in
use almost constantly.

In  the  main  room,  @{I}Holger  Kruse@{UI} (@{B}Miami@{UB}) was there, as was @{I}Chris Aldi@{UI} (@{B}Finale
Developement@{UB}, @{B}New York@{UB}, @{B}Quill@{UB}, @{B}Voodoo@{UB}, etc), @{I}Kermit Woodall@{UI} (@{B}ImageFX@{UB}, @{B}Aladdin4D@{UB})
as  well  as  @{I}Paul  Nolan@{UI}  (@{B}Photogenics_NG@{UB})  and  a  few others I can't remember
(sorry),  various  magazines  (@{B}Amazing@{UB},  @{B}Informer@{UB}) and services (@{B}Amigazone@{UB}--@{I}Harv
Laser@{UI}),  and  the user groups also had booths as well as a few retail outlets (I
got  @{B}Genetic  Species@{UB}).  Business seemed to be brisk; people were walking around
with bags full of stuff and wearing new t-shirts as well.

The seminars seemed to be well attended. I sat in when @{I}Carl@{UI} gave his second talk
about  @{B}REBOL@{UB},  and  also the demos/discussions with @{I}Chris Aldi@{UI} and @{I}Paul Nolan@{UI} (I
*really* want @{B}Photogenics_NG@{UB}!!) and the rooms were packed.

The  mood  was  very  positive  and  upbeat in stark contrast to the last show I
attended in '92 (@{B}WOA@{UB}) Pasadena.

Neither  @{I}Jeff  Shindler@{UI}, @{I}Joe Torre@{UI}, @{I}Fleecy Moss@{UI}, nor @{I}Alan Havemose@{UI} could attend.
We  were told they were at very important meetings/negotiations but no more than
that.  Attending from @{B}Amiga Inc@{UB} were @{I}Darrick Lisle@{UI}, Events Co-ordinator and @{I}Bill
McEwen@{UI} head of marketing and software evangalist.

The  following,  in no particular order (I've only had 8 hours sleep in the past
three days) is the information I gathered while there:
 * The rumor of an @{B}IBM@{UB} buyout of @{B}Gateway@{UB} is false
 * The rumor of @{B}BE@{UB} buying out @{B}Amiga Inc@{UB} is false
 * The  information  in  the  @{B}Investment Business Weekly@{UB} was badly misquoted and
   therefore is not correct.

@{B}Gateway@{UB}  is  not  for  sale.  @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} is not for sale. (@{I}Carl@{UI} added that @{B}REBOL@{UB}
isn't for sale either)

Speaking  of  @{B}REBOL@{UB},  there  should  be a general version available early in the
fall, with @{B}Amiga@{UB} one of the first platforms supported.

Re: @{B}OS5.0@{UB}

The  kernal  to be used is the @{B}Amiga@{UB} kernal. They will be using @{B}Exec@{UB}. There will
be direct @{B}Java@{UB} support (@{B}JVM@{UB}) as well as support for @{B}OpenGL@{UB}.

A  developer  program  will  be  set up soon, projected date August (this year).
@{B}Amiga  Inc@{UB}  wants  ALL developers and developer wannabees to come and sign up on
their  site. There will be a special area (password protected) for developers to
get  and  exchange  information.  Anyone  who  is  even  slightly  interested is
encouraged to sign up (this was emphasized).

I  don't have much on the @{B}MMC@{UB}. There were some rather specific specs shown but I
couldn't  get  them written down fast enough... (sorry) they will also be posted
on  @{B}Amiga  Inc@{UB}'s  pages soon. We were told the chip was NOT being made by @{B}Intel@{UB},
@{B}Cyrix@{UB}  (sp?)  or  @{B}AMD@{UB}.  When I get more specific information I shall, of course,
post it.

We  were  also  told that @{B}Windows@{UB} would NOT be on the development machine (@{B}Amiga
Bridge OS4.0@{UB}). @{I}"No money to @{B}Microsoft@{UB}"@{UI} is a direct quote.

@{I}Bill  McEwen@{UI}  said  that if anyone had any questions, he'd be more than happy to
answer them. You can contact him at @{I}bm@amigainc.com@{UI}. He said he would answer all
polite  mail.  He  also said he'd not answer any rude or nasty mail but that *he
would keep it*.

Speaking  of development. @{I}Olaf Bartel@{UI} (sp?) has been doing extensive work in the
@{B}Development  CD@{UB}  and the @{B}RKM@{UB}s, they have been bugfixed and upgraded (now @{B}version
2.1@{UB}). This should be available soon.

@{I}Dave  Haynie@{UI}  has  also  released  a  lot  of  information.  It  can be found on
@{B}http://www.thule.no/haynie/@{UB}. There will be more.

@{I}Denny Atkins@{UI} is coming back to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

There  might  be a bit more, but I'm getting really tired... If I remember more,
or  get  more  clarification,  I shall pass it on to you. I did have a wonderful
time,  despite the heat and some physical problems, and I feel more hopeful than
ever about the future of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

@{UI}asha@mindless.com@{UI}
Charter Member: @{B}Team *AMIGA*@{UB} UIN#14766598
