@node art04 "INTERVIEW WITH VULCAN'S MARBLE-EYES DEVELOPMENT TEAM"

INTERVIEW WITH @{B}VULCAN@{UB}'S @{B}MARBLE-EYES DEVELOPMENT@{UB} TEAM
----------------------------------------------------

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE@{UI}

@{I}Q:  I  remember  downloading  a  preview  of @{B}Genetic Species@{UB} from @{B}Aminet@{UB} made by
@{B}Ambrosia@{UB} and now you are called @{B}Marble-Eyes@{UB} what has happened?@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB}  Our  full name is @{B}Marble-Eyes Development@{UB}. Our game started as a good demo
effect, but at this point our coder was more or less alone on this project and a
member  of  the  demogroup called @{B}Ambrosia@{UB}. The @{B}Genetic Species@{UB} engine was first
shown the @{B}Gathering 96@{UB} in Norway and got a lot of positive criticism. After this
event  the  other  members  in  @{B}Ambrosia@{UB}  seem  to  care  more  about other demo
productions,  and the coder was therefore forced into an alternative arrangement
of finding someone to do the job.
Finally  a  very  talented graphician reply an e-mail and process began to speed
up.  Later  on  @{I}Martin  Halberg@{UI} our audioman joined the team and our demo effect
began  to  look  a lot more like a game. We all decided to leave behind the demo
scene  and concentrate on game development, therefore it seem natural to restart
under a new name.

@{I}Q: When did Vulcan Software get into the picture?@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB}  The demo from the @{B}Gathering 96@{UB} was put on @{B}Aminet@{UB} and downloaded by @{B}Vulcan@{UB}.
They  liked  it  and  saw  potential  in it's concept so they contacted us and a
contract was signed on 1st of December 1996.

@{I}Q: Try to describe @{B}Genetic Species@{UB} using 50 words.@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB} Based on @{B}Paradroid@{UB} this game offers furiously invigorating and thrilling 3d
action  with  an amount of details not seen on the @{B}Amiga@{UB} for along time. Lots of
puzzles,  atmosphere  and  gameplay. 200 MB intro animation, 30 mins of CD music
and 29000 lines of optimised @{B}68k@{UB} assembler.

@{I}Q:  46  words  that's  close  ;).  The @{B}Amiga@{UB} has seen many @{B}Doom@{UB} clones, is there
anything new about your game?@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB} The speed, the playability, the atmosphere and support for everything worth
a  mention.  Not at least your unique ability (and need) to take over the bodies
of  humans,  cyborgs  and  droids,  which  has  proven to work very well in a 3d
environment. We believe it is unfair to call @{B}GS@{UB} for a @{B}Doom@{UB} clone. In fact we use
the  3d  environment  as a platform to build an adventure game. Imagine the year
2034  you  startup your big virtual reality machine and enters a cyberspace with
no boundaries. Would you say: "awesome @{B}Doom@{UB} clone man!"

@{I}Q: Why do you think @{B}Genetic Species@{UB} is better than other 3d games?@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB}  @{B}GS@{UB}  features  a  original  plot  that  is well combined with the story and
gameplay.  The  plot  in  the  game  is  not just for decoration. Once you start
playing  a  weak  and  twisted story line begins to unfold. Shooting every thing
that moves will get you nowhere and that gives @{B}Genetic Species@{UB} the edge.

@{I}Q: Tell us a secret no one outside @{B}Marble-Eyes@{UB} knows!@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB}  We  are  aliens  from Alpha Centauri and have made plans to rule the world
before the millennium.

@{I}Q: What can we expect from @{B}Marble-Eyes@{UB} in the future?@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB}  Well, we are here to stay! Our motivation and passion for computer science
continues  and  we have big plans for @{B}Genetic Species@{UB} before we start on another
game.  First  up is a multiplayer AddOn with TCP/IP support. This means that you
will  be  able  to  play  over  the internet. We hope to create the first useful
internet  game  for  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB},  if not Mr. @{I}Burkey@{UI} beats us there. However this
multiplayer  AddOns  will  be  infected  with  all  sort  of  pirate protections
something  we  didn't have time to do on the CD-ROM. With 4 years of demo coding
experience and reverse engineering of demos I should be able to give the cracker
and good headache and at the time this AddOn is cracked a new one is out.

@{I}Q: Speaking of piracy. How is Genetic Species doing?@{UI}
@{B}MeD:@{UB} We haven't done anything to prevent piracy yet, but the size of the game is
more  than  600  MB  which  makes a natural limit for BBS/Internet piracy. Still
there  are jerks out there who rather will spent two days online than to support
the  future  of  the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. However most people are supporting an @{B}Amiga@{UB} specific
game. An issue our sales at the @{B}WOA@{UB} show outlined in style!

Live Long & Prosper!
@{I}Paul Carrington@{UI} BA (Hons)
@{B}Vulcan Software Limited@{UB}

Commercial: @{B}www.vulcan.co.uk@{UB}
Promotional: @{B}www.vul-soft.demon.co.uk@{UB}
