@node art05 "RUMOR CONTROL FROM BILL MCEWEN, HEAD OF MARKETING"

RUMOR CONTROL FROM @{I}BILL MCEWEN@{UI}, HEAD OF MARKETING
-------------------------------------------------

August 26,1998

Greetings:

I  want  to  thank  all  of you who have contacted me in the last couple of days
about  some  new  rumors  that  are  spreading  through our community. As I have
mentioned  before if you have any questions please do not hesitate in contacting
any of us listed at the end of this message.

Here are the rumors that are circulating this week:

 * @{I}The new @{B}Amiga@{UB} will be based on the @{B}Intel Merced@{UB} chip.@{UI}
   WRONG!  I  want  to  make  this perfectly clear. The next generation of @{B}Amiga@{UB}
   machines  that  run  @{B}OS 5.0@{UB} will typically be media-processor based. The last
   time I checked @{B}Intel@{UB} didn't have one of these.

 * @{I}Fleecy and I are dating.@{UI}
   I will answer this one later.

 * @{I}The @{B}BeOS@{UB} is the OS partner, and they are what everyone should develop to.@{UI}
   WRONG!  Please  do not jump at every rumor. As mentioned before, @{B}Be@{UB} is ONE of
   the OS partners that we are considering. There are at least 6 others that are
   on the list. We have narrowed the contenders, and we hope to have all of this
   wrapped up soon.

 * @{I}Amiga  has  no  plans for the high end of the platform, and will not have any
   support for NewTek.@{UI}
   WRONG!  Keys  to  our  success  are  the ability of the next generation @{B}Amiga@{UB}
   architecture  to  be  scaleable and work well as a home computer and the high
   end with the @{B}Toaster@{UB} and @{B}Flyer@{UB}.

 * @{I}@{B}Amiga@{UB}  does not care about the @{B}QuikPak@{UB} situation, and does not care about the
   @{B}4000@{UB} shortage.@{UI}
   WRONG!  We are doing all that we can in helping this process come to a close.
   The  legal  problems  are  between  @{B}QuikPak@{UB} and @{I}Hembach@{UI}. These legal problems
   started  before  @{B}Gateway@{UB} ever purchased @{B}Amiga@{UB}. We hope and pray that this can
   be resolved quickly also.

 * @{I}Jeff and I are dating.@{UI}
   WRONG! It would make @{I}Fleecy@{UI} jealous.

 * @{I}@{B}OS 3.5@{UB} is back and in development.@{UI}
   We  are currently evaluating the market needs for an OS upgrade before @{B}OS 5.0@{UB}
   ships.  No  decision has been made. As soon as we have all of our information
   gathered, we will make the final decision and let everyone know.

 * @{I}@{B}Amiga Classic@{UB} is only for those machines compatible with @{B}OS 4.0@{UB}.@{UI}
   WRONG!  The  @{B}Amiga  Classic@{UB}  line  is  for the applications and hardware that
   currently run @{B}OS 3.1@{UB}. If it runs @{B}3.1@{UB} then it is in the @{B}Classic@{UB} series.

 * @{I}The  new  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  architecture  will  not be compatible with the current @{B}Amiga@{UB}
   applications@{UI}.
   We  plan  to  have  hardware  and  software  compatibility  for the developer
   platform and software emulation for @{B}OS 5.0@{UB}.

I  hope  that  this helps in dispelling some of the rumors. I am sure that there
are  more,  and  once I receive a rumor from more than a few people, we will get
the answers up as quickly as possible.

Thank  you again, and I look forward to seeing many of you in Columbus, and then
Cologne.

Keeping the faith,

@{I}Bill McEwen@{UI}
Head of Marketing, @{B}Amiga, Inc.@{UB}
